The impact on American Express's Membership Rewards liability in 2024 was an increase of $1.01 billion (from $13.74 billion in 2023 to $14.75 billion in 2024), driven by a higher Ultimate Redemption Rate (URR) and slightly elevated redemption costs due to shifts in Card Member redemption mix (e.g., more redemptions for higher-cost rewards). To address these changes, the company refined its liability estimation methodology by:  
1) Updating statistical and actuarial models for URR to reflect evolving redemption trends, product mix, and partner contract changes;  
2) Adjusting the weighted average cost (WAC) per point assumption to account for non-representative short-term cost fluctuations, ensuring alignment with long-term redemption cost expectations;  
3) Periodically reassessing assumptions in response to developments in third-party partner arrangements and redemption patterns, including changes in proprietary card portfolios.
